  <div class="tips-card">
    <h3>Tips for Building Great Spice Blends</h3>
    <div class="tips-grid">
      <div class="tip-item">
        <h4>Toast Before Grinding</h4>
        <p>Dry-toast whole spices in a skillet over medium heat for 1-2 minutes until fragrant. This releases essential oils and deepens flavor dramatically.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-item">
        <h4>Balance the Four Pillars</h4>
        <p>Great blends balance heat (chili, pepper), warmth (cinnamon, cumin), brightness (citrus peel, sumac), and depth (cloves, star anise).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-item">
        <h4>Start Small with Strong Spices</h4>
        <p>Cloves, star anise, and nutmeg dominate quickly. Start with small amounts and increase. You can always add more but can't remove.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-item">
        <h4>Store Properly</h4>
        <p>Keep blends in airtight glass jars away from heat and light. Label with date made. Ground blends stay potent for 3-6 months.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-item">
        <h4>Layer Your Seasoning</h4>
        <p>Add half the blend at the start of cooking for depth and the rest near the end for bright, fresh flavor. This creates complexity.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tip-item">
        <h4>Record Your Winners</h4>
        <p>When you create a blend you love, save the recipe card. Small ratio changes make big differences, so exact proportions matter.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

